President Barack Obama has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the funeral of former President Kim Dae-jung in Seoul, Republic of Korea. The delegation will be led by the Honorable Madeleine K. Albright, Former Secretary of State. Other members of the delegation include U.S. Ambassador to the Republic of Korea, Kathleen Stephens, The Legal Adviser of the U.S. Department of State, Harold Koh, and Special Representative for North Korea Policy, Stephen W. Bosworth. Former U.S. Ambassador to the Republic of Korea, Donald P. Gregg, and Former U.S. Ambassador to the Republic of Korea, Thomas C. Hubbard, are also part of the delegation. Additionally, Former U.S. Ambassador to the Republic of Korea, James Laney, Former U.S. Representative Jim Leach, President of the Korea Society Evans Revere, Former Counselor of the U.S. Department of State Wendy R. Sherman, and Vice Chair of the Albright Stonebridge Group are part of the delegation.